  "tool_calls": [
    {
      "name": "Skill",
      "args": {
        "skill": "stm32agent",
        "args": "Release the VCP port so the user can open it in minicom."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 vcp close",
        "description": "Release the VCP port so minicom can take over"
      }
    }
  ],
  "final_text": "That's a clean VCP-close \u2014 one command:\nVCP port released. The substrate has closed its handle \u2014 minicom (or any other terminal tool) can now open the port directly. When you're done in minicom and want the substrate to take over again, run `stm32 vcp reconnect` or just issue the next `stm32 vcp tail` / `stm32 vcp send` command and it will auto-attach (SB-001)."
}